				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">---------------------------------------------
<br />
Why only evils?
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
This underutilized camp in Ocean of Tears is only for those who don't really care about killing some serious faction in exchange for steady, uninterrupted experience. It's quiet, remote, and often you have the entire zone to yourself, though occasionally you have to deal with /oocs from people arguing about Gornit, the seafuries, or the AC.
<br />

<br />
However, don't ever expect to go to Kaladim or the good elven lands and be welcome. Here are all the factions you slaughter by doing this camp:
<br />

<br />
Killing dwarves:
<br />
- Kaladim Citizen (guards in BB still potentially OK)
<br />

<br />
Killing green Sisters of Erollisi, named sisters such as Antimine and Tegea Prendyn: 
<br />
- Clerics of Tunare (Felwithe clerics, paladins, some guards)
<br />
- Faydark's Champions (Kelethin rangers and merchants)
<br />
- King Tearis Thex (various Felwithe inhabitants, including some guards)
<br />
- Soldiers of Tunare (Kelethin druids)
<br />
(raises Crushbone Orcs, if you even care)
<br />

<br />
There are also two low level pirates named Dayle Jornin and Zyle Bensmill, who have huge aggro radiuses and will attack without provocation:
<br />
- Pirates of Gunthak
<br />
(raises Firiona Vie)
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />
Prepare for camp
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
You need to take the boat from East Freeport. If you are KOS in East Freeport, you will need to invis yourself to the dock. It's not a bad idea to bind yourself on the dock in case of a CR. Even if you are KOS, you are safe at the very end of the dock.
<br />

<br />
If you want to bind in OOT, there are a few safe spots on Sister Island. However, you will have to take the boat all the way to Butcherblock to get out of the zone, or go to Brother Island and pick up the boat there. Both will require invisibility, because after killing the elves, neither the Brothers nor the Sisters will like you very much.
<br />

<br />
SoW potions are helpful here, especially once you have started killing the sisters along with the dwarves.
<br />

<br />
If you are not KOS to the elves initially (and you soon will be, so don't get used to this), you can just wait until the boat docks at Sister Island and disembark. However, if you are KOS to the elves, you will need to jump off the boat when you see the island off the right side of the boat (north). Swim to the eastern shore and you will see plenty of spots where you can get on dry land and make a pet in relative peace.
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />
What's good about this camp?
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
The experience here is not super fast -- not as fast as some other camps. However, it's quiet, with plenty of safe places to sit and med for very steady experience with little to no competition. The spawn you will be hunting -- two dwarves and two named sisters -- are spaced out so there is very little chance of adds. The green Sisters of Erollisi will generally not attack you unless you are right on top of them, and even then they are an easy kill. 
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />
Pets for this camp
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
I used the earth pet because everything here runs (and runs fast) and root becomes important. There are a few EXTREMELY nasty mobs on this island that will add if your targets run out of control, so you want to keep them nailed down whenever possible. Of course, use Burnout and shield of flame, and load your pet with summoned goodies.
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />
Strategy for the dwarves
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
Your first targets are going to be two dwarves, a male named Hugan Tunbin (level 25) who spawns near the shore, and a female named Elona Tunbin (level 24), who spawns nearby near a stone monument.  DO NOT CONFUSE THEM WITH THE DWARVES THAT SPAWN ON THE WEST SHORE. Those are all male, there are 3 of them, and one of them, Glendl Vargnus, will clean your clock -- he's level 45 and NOT to be messed with at this time.
<br />

<br />
The Tunbins are located on the northeast part of Sister Island. They are warriors, mildly magic resistant, and supremely stupid. As a human Innoruuk worshipping mage, they conned dubious to me when I started, and after three levels of killing them, they still conned dubious. Although they ruin Kaladim Citizen faction by killing them, they don't seem to be on that faction themselves, so as far as I can tell you can kill them indefinitely under those circumstances and they won't aggro you first.
<br />

<br />
Both can easily be killed in place, although I recommend getting malise on them as early as you can manage it so your pet's root sticks. They seemed slightly less resistant to the Blade line of nukes than to the fire line.
<br />

<br />
The one thing you need to be careful of with Elona Tunbin is that both Dayle Jornin and Zyle Bensmill spawn fairly close by. These are low level (16-20) but they have a huge aggro radius and will attack on sight, running from fairly long distances to do so. They usually spawn west and a little north of Elona. If you see one of them up, send the pet to get him out of the way first so he doesn't add and interrupt your spells. They're not tough, but they can be annoying. You can also try pulling Elona due south a bit and that will usually keep the pirates from adding.
<br />

<br />
The Tunbins drop small amounts of cash, occasional research items (mostly necro words or runes), dwarf blood, and dwarf meat.
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />
Strategy for elves
<br />
---------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
For the most part, you can ignore the wandering Sisters of Erollisi. They are low level (9-13) but they do drop some spell components, wood elf parts, elf blood, and purity belts, which sell back for about 2pp each. Of course, there is no merchant in this zone who will deal with you, either.
<br />

<br />
Once you've gotten the hang of the dwarf camp and you have a lot of time you're sitting around doing nothing, it's time to add in a named Sister or two. There are really only two you are going to have time to do, and only two that are really safe to pull.
<br />

<br />
Run south and then west along the shore of the island until you can just see the village. You will see a large tree and then just beyond it a female half-elf in silver chain. Have your pet /guard here at the tree, and then run and fetch the elf, bringing her back to the tree. Her name is Antinime, she is level 22-24, and she will screw your elf faction royally. She is also a melee, does not cast, and is somewhat magic resistant. She drops purity belts, wood elf parts, elven blood, and the occasional rusty weapon.
<br />

<br />
Kill Antinime fairly quickly if you can. If you have the resources for it, your next kill is Tegea Prendyn.
<br />

<br />
This is a trickier pull and MUST be done carefully or else you will get two other named sisters with her from nearby. If you're really unlucky, you'll get even more. 
<br />

<br />
Tegea Prendyn stands on the end of the dock. Follow the edge of the water until you're in range of Tegea; you'll have to go very close to dock to get this close. Pull her with malise and then run back, CAREFULLY, right along the edge of the water to path her through the water and onto the shore. If she paths through the village, you might as well gate.
<br />

<br />
Once Tegea Prendyn is to your pet, it's just a routine kill. Like Antinime, she is not a caster. She's level 25 and hits a bit harder than Antinime, though her drops are pretty much the same.
<br />

<br />
By this time, you should be able to run back to the dwarves, and mana permitting, start that pull, or have a few minutes to med a little and rebuff your pet for the next round.
<br />

<br />
...Csimene<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.breedlist.com/personal/csimene.gif"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
